setup steps
===========

* install Ubuntu
* append this to /etc/sudoers:
kevan ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL
* sudo apt install redshift i3 sway rofi tmux neovim git git-delta build-essential clang curl pipx
* pipx install tldr
* curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh
* sudo apt install cmake g++ pkg-config libfontconfig1-dev libxcb-xfixes0-dev libxkbcommon-dev python3
* cargo install alacritty ripgrep fd-find jj-cli

* install and configure keyd -- https://github.com/rvaiya/keyd
* install 1password: https://1password.com/downloads/linux
* set up ssh keys -- create new ones, and tell github to trust them
* clone this repo
* run update_configs
* log out and back in

* download & install chrome -- https://www.google.com/chrome/
    * load blank new tab page extension
* download & install vs code -- https://code.visualstudio.com/
* uninstall snap -- sudo apt purge snapd

situational:
* change grub timeout to 2 seconds
* if you're dual-booting windows:
    timedatectl set-local-rtc 1
